sce <- readRDS("/mnt/nmorais-nfs/marta/pA_karine/r_session/e12h-preliminary-analysis/macrophage_subset/data/sce-macrophages.rds")
design <- model.matrix(~ 0 + sce$condition)
limma <- removeBatchEffect(assays(sce)$logcounts, batch=sce$dataset, design = design)
assays(sce)$limma_dataset <- limma
total_counts <- colSums(assays(sce)$limma_dataset)
total_counts[1:5]
## AAACCCAAGTGGAAGA-1_mct1 AAACCCACAGTGTGGA-1_mct1 AAACCCAGTTGGTACT-1_mct1 
##                6370.127                5628.815                5370.586 
## AAACGAAAGATCACTC-1_mct1 AAACGAACACGGATCC-1_mct1 
##                6158.004                6696.994
check_countMatrix <- counts(sce) > 0
total_features <- colSums(check_countMatrix)
df5 <- data.frame(total_counts = total_counts,
                 total_features = total_features,
                 sample = sce$sample,
                 sorting = sce$sorting,
                 condition = sce$condition,
                 dataset = sce$dataset)
df6 <- data.frame(log10_total_counts = log10(total_counts),
                    log10_total_features = log10(total_features),
                  sample = sce$sample,
                  sorting = sce$sorting,
                  dataset = sce$dataset)
make_barplot <- function(df, x, y, title, ylab){
  ggplot(df, aes(x=x, y=y, fill=x)) +
  
  geom_violin(show.legend = FALSE) + 
  theme_bw() +
  theme(text = element_text(size=20), axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  ylab(ylab) + xlab("Sample") +
  scale_fill_manual(values=sample_colors) +
    ggtitle(title)
}
sample_colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "yellow3", "pink", "red", "dodgerblue", "coral1",
                   "purple", "magenta", "cyan", "grey")
make_barplot(df5, df5$dataset, df5$total_counts, "All samples", "Library size") 

make_barplot(df6, df6$dataset, df6$log10_total_counts, "All samples", "Library size (log10)") +ylim(3.5,4)

make_barplot(df5, df5$sample, df5$total_counts, "All samples", "Library size") 

make_barplot(df6, df6$sample, df6$log10_total_counts, "All samples", "Library size (log10)") +ylim(3.5,4)

make_barplot(df5, df5$sorting, df5$total_counts, "All samples", "Library size") 

make_barplot(df6, df6$sorting, df6$log10_total_counts, "All samples", "Library size (log10)") +ylim(3.5,4)
